                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid red, reddish-brown)</seg>
                        Priest
                        (qasis ) Takla Hāymānot is mentioned as the scribe in Additio 1.<date>First
                           half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ጊዮር፡ or ጊዮርጊ፡</abbr> for <expan>ጊዮርጊስ፡ </expan> (e.g. <locus target="#37v">37v</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Divine names; name of the protagonist; name of the
                           donors and their relatives; incipit of Texts I, II and III; incipit of
                           each miracle in Text III; incipits of chapters in Text II; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 A few groups
                           of lines (alternating with black lines) in the incipit pages of Texts I
                           and III (fols. 4r, 93r).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#108vb">f. 108vb</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘዓድሐ፡ ዘወሀብዎ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡
                              መዓጔ፡ ዘስሞሙ፡ ወልደ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወልደ፡ ሰማዕት፡ ወልደ፡ ሩፋኤል፡ ወልደ፡ ሕይወት፡ ገብረ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡
                              &lt;...&gt; ከመ፡ ይኩኖሙ፡ መድኀኒተ፡ ለነፍሶሙ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡
                              ውጉዞ፡ ለይኩን፡ ወበቃለ፡ ዚአየኒ፡ አነ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወጸሐፊሐ፡ ውጉዞ፡ ለይኩን፡ ወገበዝሂ፡
                              መምሕሬ፡ ገብረ፡ ጊዮርጊስ።</q>
                           <note> The note mentions the names of the donors, Walda
                           Hāymānot, Walda Samāʿǝt, Walda Rufāʾel, Walda Ḥǝywat and Gabra Giyorgis;
                           the name of the church to which the Ms. was donated, Giyorgis Maʿāgʷe,
                           and the name of the scribe, qasis Takla Hāymānot. The name of the
                              gabaz, Gabra Giyorgis, is also mentioned. The meaning of the word
                              "ʿadḥa", mentioned at the beginning of the note, is not clear. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc> Corrections and omissions written in the margins: <locus target="#9r">9r</locus>, 30r, 31r, 32r, 32v, 37r, 45r, 47v, 51r, 70r,
                           79r, 81r, 84v, 86v, 92v, 100r.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc> Names of the donors and their
                           relatives written in red in the upper margins: <locus target="#98v">98v</locus>, 102v, 103r, 103v, 105v, 106v, 107r, 108v.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Tamallas-sign in the shape of ┴ written in the text, indicating the place
                           where the omission, written in the margins in the main hand, belongs:
                              <locus target="#9ra">9ra</locus>, 22ra, 30ra, 32rb, 32vb, 45ra, 47vb,
                           51ra, 70ra, 81rb, 84va, 86va, 92vb, 99va, 100rb, 102va, 103rb, 103vb,
                           105va, 106va, 107ra, 108va.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"><desc>Writing exercises: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 1v, 2r, 2v.
 - Crude note: <locus target="#110r">110r</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"><desc>Doodles: <locus target="#109r">109r</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e6"><desc>Numbers of pages are written on the recto of
                           folios in blue pen in a crude secondary hand from <locus target="#4r">4r</locus> to <locus target="#64r">64r</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Monthly readings are indicated by the names of the
                              months and one exact date, enclosed in a frame or between two lines,
